# River Map

The river map simply marks rivers on the map. On top of being necessary in HOI4 (if your map has any rivers, that is), this data can be used in province generation so that province boundaries go along rivers.

## How do I make a river map?

For more detailed information, [check out the Hearts of Iron 4 wiki!](https://hoi4.paradoxwikis.com/Map_modding#River_map)

### Creating the base river map

#### Generating a base river map in HOI4 UMT

You can generate a base river map in HOI4 UMT after loading in your Land Input Image. You can then save this map by right clicking the image and selecting **Save As...**

The outputted river map is a bitmap image file (.BMP) with a bit depth of 8. You can open this image file in any image editor which supports editing bitmap files.

#### Creating your own river map base from scratch

Creating your own river map base from scratch is **hard**, and requires knowing the exact 8-bit color palette that Paradox used.

**If you insist**, you could open the original HOI4 river map (Hearts of Iron 4\map\rivers.bmp), and just clear all data on the image, resize it to your map's size and use that to draw your rivers. But you have been warned. Remember to not accidentally overwrite the original rivers.bmp.

If you decide to do so, here are the colors for land, sea and lakes:

### Saving the river map

The river map should be in Indexed mode and saved as a **8-bit bitmap image file (.BMP)**. 8-bit meaning the **bit depth**.

### Loading the river map into HOI4 UMT

Click on the panel on the right, and select the saved river map from wherever you saved it.

If your bitmap is not saved in the correct format, HOI4 UMT will attempt to load and convert it to the correct format, **but this can fail if the format doesn't match at all**. For everything to go smoothly, *please* save it in the correct format.
